1) To get webob v1.2+ to be in Python's path, add a webob.pth file to the /usr/lib/<python>/site-packages directory with the name of the webob egg directory in it.

2) To get /var/www/html/afmap/mturk in Python's path:
a) create /etc/profile.d/mappingafrica.[c]sh containing the necessary definitions:
tcsh:
setenv PYTHONPATH "/var/www/html/afmap/mturk"
bash:
export PYTHONPATH="/var/www/html/afmap/mturk"

b) add the following lines to /etc/sysconfig/httpd:
umask 007
PYTHONPATH="/var/www/html/afmap/mturk"
export PYTHONPATH

3) To easily access pgadmin3 v9.1, create /etc/profile.d/postgresql.[c]sh containing:
tcsh:
setenv PATH "/usr/pgsql-9.1/bin:$PATH"
bash:
export PATH="/usr/pgsql-9.1/bin:$PATH"
